      "writtenOn": "2020-12-03T15:57:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "layer.matrix() always just returned the device\u0027s local to device matrix.\n\nlayer.clipBounds() actually returned device-\u003egetGlobalBounds(), but I think there were two subtle bugs. \n1: getGlobalBounds() transformed (0,0,devW, devH) by its device-to-global matrix, but didn\u0027t actually factor in its clip bounds at all.\n2: the clip rect stored in the saved canvas state is later applied to a new SkCanvas that represents the device. It\u0027s done before setting the saved local-to-device matrix, so the clip rect should be in the device\u0027s coordinate space. getGlobalBounds() was in the global coordinate space, so would be slightly off if we had a device with a non (0,0) origin.\n\ndevClipBounds() should just fix both of these issues.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 212,
        "startChar": 41,
        "endLine": 212,
        "endChar": 89
      },
      "revId": "876162419a4ed1089635feb2cbd007c85897cffb",
